gw.api.databuilder.populator

Interface PackagedValue

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    PackagedArrayValue

    public interface PackagedValue
    Represents a data value stored on a builder. Generally, values in builders are not stored in their "raw" form, but instead are stored in a "packaged" form. At "populate" time, the packaged value can be "unpackaged" for consumption by a BeanPopulator. For example, Beans may be stored as Keys to existing beans, or as DataBuilders of future beans.
    Author:
    pdalbora
    See Also:
